  "title": "WATCH: Governor, mayor, US representatives address Ruidoso recovery",
  "text": "WATCH: Governor, mayor, US representatives address Ruidoso recovery\nRUIDOSO, N.M. — Two days after flooding devastated Ruidoso, New Mexico Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham, Mayor Lynn Crawford and two U.S. representatives addressed recovery efforts.\nThe mayor said Thursday the flooding damaged “200-400 homes,” compared to 35-50 initially.\n“After yesterday [Wednesday], it become very apparent that there was a lot more damage than we assumed and what we thought in the beginning. So those things have come in the door, we’ve had to take a set back to move forward,” the mayor said.\nThe flooding impacted as many as 100-150 local Ruidoso families.\nWatch the full press conference in the video here:",
